<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ '/styles/domino-checker.css' | url }}">

<h2 class="main-header">Domino Checker</h2>

<p class="no-indent lead">
	Upload a Blokus contraption image (black walls, white start cells, colored wires).
	The solver finds final domino tilings with a given number of placed cells.
</p>

<ol>
	<li>Image format: opaque pixels only; <strong>black</strong> = walls, <strong>white</strong> = start cells, other colors = wires.</li>
	<li><strong>Target cells</strong> defaults to 18 (must be even, since each domino covers 2 cells).</li>
	<li><strong>Solve</strong> runs in the browser; <strong>Stop</strong> aborts the search.</li>
	<li>Solutions appear as downloadable PNGs with a gray overlay on placed cells.</li>
</ol>

<div id="domino-checker-root"></div>

<script src="{{ '/js/domino-checker.browser.js' | url }}" data-auto-app="false" defer></script>
<script defer>
	document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
		window.DominoChecker.createApp(document.getElementById("domino-checker-root"));
	});
</script>
